text.tspan: The decline of transport and communication costs relative to 1930, World,
Sea freight corresponds to average international freight charges per tonne. Passenger air transport corresponds to average

to cost of a three-minute call from New York to London.
Source: Transaction Costs - OECD Economic Outlook (2007)
